Deep Learning Course - Assignment 2

Q3. Corporación Favorita Grocery Sales Forecasting

Submitted by: Itay Bouganim and Ido Rom

Problem Statement

Brick-and-mortar grocery stores are always in a delicate dance with purchasing and sales forecasting. Predict a little over, and grocers are stuck with overstocked, perishable goods.
Guess a little under, and popular items quickly sell out, leaving money on the table and customers fuming.

The problem becomes more complex as retailers add new locations with unique needs, new products, ever transitioning seasonal tastes, and unpredictable product marketing.
Corporación Favorita, a large Ecuadorian-based grocery retailer, knows this all too well. They operate hundreds of supermarkets, with over 200,000 different products on their shelves.

Task Description

Corporación Favorita has challenged the Kaggle community to build a model that more accurately forecasts product sales.
They currently rely on subjective forecasting methods with very little data to back them up and very little automation to execute plans.
They’re excited to see how machine learning could better ensure they please customers by having just enough of the right products at the right time.

Corporación Favorita Grocery Sales Forecasting on kaggle dataset link

# Utility function to load local images as HTML in base64 encoding
def display_image(path, label=None):
    import base64, io
    from IPython.core.display import display, HTML
    from PIL import Image as PILImage

    image = PILImage.open(path)

    output = io.BytesIO()
    image.save(output, format='PNG')
    encoded_string = base64.b64encode(output.getvalue()).decode()

    html = '<img src="data:image/png;base64,{}"/>'.format(encoded_string) if label is None else '<div style="text-align: center;">{}<img src="data:image/png;base64,{}" width="200" height="200"/></div>'.format(label, encoded_string)
    display(HTML(html))

from tqdm import tqdm 

def interpolate_nan_values(data):
    for column in tqdm(data.columns, desc="Interpolating data columns containing NaN"):
        if data[column].isnull().values.any():
            data[column] = data[column].interpolate(method='linear', limit_direction='both')
    return data


def prob_to_true_false(trues, falses):
  rand = random.uniform(0, 1)
  false_prob = falses / (trues + falses)
  if rand < false_prob:
    return False
  return True

def create_model():
  store_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  item_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')

  store_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(store_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(store_nbr_inp)
  item_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(item_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(item_nbr_inp)

  x = concatenate([store_nbr_emb,item_nbr_emb])
  x = Flatten()(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dense(10,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dense(10,activation='relu')(x)
  x = Dense(1,activation='relu')(x)
  nn_model = Model([store_nbr_inp,item_nbr_inp],x)
  nn_model.compile(loss = 'msle',optimizer='sgd', metrics=['acc'])
  return nn_model

from os.path import join
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ModelCheckpoint, ReduceLROnPlateau
model_save_dir = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DeepLearning/Assignment2/models'

def get_callbacks(saved_model_name):
    early_stopping_callback = EarlyStopping(monitor="val_loss", patience=3, verbose=2)
    rlop_callback = ReduceLROnPlateau(patience=3)   
    checkpoint_callback = ModelCheckpoint(join(model_save_dir, f'model_{saved_model_name}.h5'), 
                                                monitor='val_loss', verbose=1, 
                                                save_best_only=True, mode='min')
    return [early_stopping_callback, checkpoint_callback, rlop_callback]

def set_callbacks(description='run1',patience=15,tb_base_logdir='./logs/'):
    cp = ModelCheckpoint('best_model_weights_{}.h5'.format(description),save_best_only=True)
    es = EarlyStopping(patience=patience,monitor='val_loss')
    rlop = ReduceLROnPlateau(patience=5)   
    tb = TensorBoard(log_dir='{}{}'.format(tb_base_logdir,description))
#     cycl = CyclicLR(max_lr=0.03,step_size=5000)
    cb = [cp,es,tb,rlop]
    return cb

def plot_history(history, plot_title):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=1, figsize=(18, 6))
    
    # Plot training & validation accuracy values
    # axes[0].plot(history['accuracy'])
    # axes[0].plot(history['val_accuracy'])
    # axes[0].set_title('Model accuracy')
    # axes[0].set_ylabel('Accuracy')
    # axes[0].set_xlabel('Epoch')
    # axes[0].legend(['Train', 'Validation'], loc='lower right')
    # axes[0].grid()

    # Plot training & validation loss values
    axes.plot(history['loss'])
    axes.plot(history['val_loss'])
    axes.set_title('Model loss')
    axes.set_ylabel('Loss')
    axes.set_xlabel('Epoch')
    axes.legend(['Train', 'Validation'], loc='upper right')
    axes.grid()
    # fig.suptitle(plot_title + " Model")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def create_concate_model():
  # date_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  store_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  item_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  onpromotion_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  family_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  class_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  perishable_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  transactions_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  city_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  # state_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  type_x_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  cluster_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  type_y_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  # locale_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  locale_name_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  transferred_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')


  # date_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(date_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(date_nbr_inp)
  store_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(store_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(store_nbr_inp)
  item_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(item_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(item_nbr_inp)
  onpromotion_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(onpromotion_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(onpromotion_nbr_inp)
  family_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(family_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(family_nbr_inp)
  class_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(class_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(class_nbr_inp)
  perishable_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(perishable_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(perishable_nbr_inp)
  transactions_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(transactions_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(transactions_nbr_inp)
  city_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(city_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(city_nbr_inp)
  # state_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(state_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(state_nbr_inp)
  type_x_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(type_x_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(type_x_nbr_inp)
  cluster_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(cluster_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(cluster_nbr_inp)
  type_y_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(type_y_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(type_y_nbr_inp)
  # locale_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(locale_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(locale_nbr_inp)
  locale_name_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(locale_name_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(locale_name_nbr_inp)
  transferred_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(transferred_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(transferred_nbr_inp)
  
  x = Concatenate()([store_nbr_emb,item_nbr_emb, onpromotion_nbr_emb, family_nbr_emb, class_nbr_emb, perishable_nbr_emb, transactions_nbr_emb, city_nbr_emb, type_x_nbr_emb, cluster_nbr_emb, type_y_nbr_emb, locale_name_nbr_emb, transferred_nbr_emb])
  x = Flatten()(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dense(256,activation='relu')(x)
  x = Dense(128,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dense(64,activation='relu')(x)
  x = Dense(32,activation='relu')(x)
  x = Dropout(0.02)(x)
  x = Dense(16,activation='relu')(x)
  x = Dense(1,activation='relu')(x)
  nn_model = Model([store_nbr_inp,item_nbr_inp, onpromotion_nbr_inp, family_nbr_inp, class_nbr_inp, perishable_nbr_inp, transactions_nbr_inp, city_nbr_inp, type_x_nbr_inp, cluster_nbr_inp, type_y_nbr_inp, locale_name_nbr_inp, transferred_nbr_inp],x)
  nn_model.compile(loss = 'msle',optimizer='sgd', metrics=['acc'])
  return nn_model

from sklearn.model_selection import KFold,StratifiedKFold

def set_callbacks(description='run1',patience=15,tb_base_logdir='./logs/'):
    cp = ModelCheckpoint('best_model_weights_{}.h5'.format(description),save_best_only=True)
    es = EarlyStopping(patience=patience,monitor='val_loss')
    rlop = ReduceLROnPlateau(patience=5)   
    tb = TensorBoard(log_dir='{}{}'.format(tb_base_logdir,description))
#     cycl = CyclicLR(max_lr=0.03,step_size=5000)
    cb = [cp,es,tb,rlop]
    return cb

def create_concate_model_lstm():
  # date_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  store_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  item_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  onpromotion_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  family_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  class_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  perishable_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  transactions_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  city_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  state_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  type_x_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  cluster_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  type_y_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  locale_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  locale_name_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')
  transferred_nbr_inp = Input(shape=(1,),dtype='int64')


  # date_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(date_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(date_nbr_inp)
  store_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(store_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(store_nbr_inp)
  item_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(item_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(item_nbr_inp)
  onpromotion_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(onpromotion_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(onpromotion_nbr_inp)
  family_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(family_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(family_nbr_inp)
  class_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(class_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(class_nbr_inp)
  perishable_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(perishable_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(perishable_nbr_inp)
  transactions_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(transactions_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(transactions_nbr_inp)
  city_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(city_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(city_nbr_inp)
  state_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(state_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(state_nbr_inp)
  type_x_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(type_x_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(type_x_nbr_inp)
  cluster_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(cluster_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(cluster_nbr_inp)
  type_y_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(type_y_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(type_y_nbr_inp)
  locale_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(locale_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(locale_nbr_inp)
  locale_name_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(locale_name_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(locale_name_nbr_inp)
  transferred_nbr_emb = Embedding(len(transferred_nbr),5,input_length=1, embeddings_regularizer=l2(1e-6))(transferred_nbr_inp)
  
  x = Concatenate()([store_nbr_emb,item_nbr_emb, onpromotion_nbr_emb, family_nbr_emb, class_nbr_emb, perishable_nbr_emb, transactions_nbr_emb, city_nbr_emb, state_nbr_emb, type_x_nbr_emb, cluster_nbr_emb, type_y_nbr_emb, locale_nbr_emb, locale_name_nbr_emb, transferred_nbr_emb])
  x = LSTM(512)(x)
  x = Flatten()(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.2)(x)

  x = Dense(256,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.1)(x)

  x = Dense(128,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.1)(x)

  x = Dense(64,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.1)(x)

  x = Dense(32,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.05)(x)

  x = Dense(16,activation='relu')(x)
  x = BatchNormalization()(x)
  x = Dropout(0.1)(x)

  x = Dense(1)(x)

  nn_model = Model([store_nbr_inp,item_nbr_inp, onpromotion_nbr_inp, family_nbr_inp, class_nbr_inp, perishable_nbr_inp, transactions_nbr_inp, city_nbr_inp, state_nbr_inp, type_x_nbr_inp, cluster_nbr_inp, type_y_nbr_inp, locale_nbr_inp, locale_name_nbr_inp, transferred_nbr_inp],x)
  nn_model.compile(loss = 'msle',optimizer='sgd', metrics=['mse', 'mae', 'msle'])
  return nn_model

from sklearn.model_selection import KFold,StratifiedKFold
from sklearn.model_selection   import train_test_split

def create_window(x, y, size, jump):
  x_ret = np.array([[x[f][i:i+size] for i in range(0, len(x[f])-size, jump)] for f in x.columns])
  y_ret = np.array([y[i:i+size] for i in range(0, len(y)-size, jump)])
  return x_ret, y_ret


def set_callbacks(description='run1',patience=15,tb_base_logdir='./logs/'):
    cp = ModelCheckpoint('best_model_weights_{}.h5'.format(description),save_best_only=True)
    es = EarlyStopping(patience=patience,monitor='val_loss')
    rlop = ReduceLROnPlateau(patience=5)   
    tb = TensorBoard(log_dir='{}{}'.format(tb_base_logdir,description))
#     cycl = CyclicLR(max_lr=0.03,step_size=5000)
    cb = [cp,es,tb,rlop]
    return cb
